\[\frac{z}{40} = \frac{x}{40} + \frac{y}{40} i\]and
\[\frac{40}{\overline{z}} = \frac{40}{x - yi} = \frac{40(x + yi)}{x^2 + y^2} = \frac{40x}{x^2 + y^2} + \frac{40y}{x^2 + y^2} i.\]Thus, the inequalities $0 \le \operatorname{Re} \left( \frac{z}{40} \right) \le 1,$ $0 \le \operatorname{Im} \left( \frac{z}{40} \right) \le 1,$ $0 \le \operatorname{Re} \left( \frac{40}{\overline{z}} \right) \le 1,$ and $0 \le \operatorname{Im} \left( \frac{40}{\overline{z}} \right) \le 1$ become
\begin{align*}
0 &\le \frac{x}{40} \le 1, \\
0 &\le \frac{y}{40} \le 1, \\
0 &\le \frac{40x}{x^2 + y^2} \le 1, \\
0 &\le \frac{40y}{x^2 + y^2} \le 1.
\end{align*}The first two inequalities imply $0 \le x \le 40$ and $0 \le y \le 40.$  The third and fourth inequalities imply
\[40x \le x^2 + y^2 \quad \text{and} \quad 40y \le x^2 + y^2.\]Completing the square in $x,$ we get
\[(x - 20)^2 + y^2 \ge 400.\]Completing the square in $y,$ we get
\[x^2 + (y - 20)^2 \ge 400.\]These inequalities describe the region outside the circles centered at $(20,0)$ and $(0,20)$ with radius 20.

